collar /ˈkɒlə/

(collars) 

1. N-COUNT The collar of a shirt or coat is the part which fits around the neck and is usually folded over. 衣领 

例： His tie was pulled loose and his collar hung open. 他的领带被扯松了，衣领敞开着。 

2.  →  see also blue-collar , white-collar 

3. N-COUNT A collar is a band of leather or plastic which is put around the neck of a dog or cat. (狗或猫的) 项圈

